@startuml
title DDD & Clean Architecture: Fixing Violations with Adapter Pattern

' --- STYLING ---
skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam boxBorderColor #CCCCCC
skinparam arrowColor #333333
skinparam participantBorderColor #333333

' --- SCENARIO 1: VIOLATIONS ---
box "Scenario A: Architecture Violations" #LightCoral
    participant "High-Level Module\n<color:white><b>(Domain Layer)</color>" as Domain_Bad
    participant "Low-Level Module\n<color:white><b>(Infrastructure Layer)</color>" as Infra_Bad
end box

Domain_Bad -> Infra_Bad : <color:white><b>saveToOracleDB(data)</b></color>

activate Infra_Bad
Infra_Bad --> Domain_Bad : <color:white>SQL Result
deactivate Infra_Bad

== Refactoring to Adapter Pattern ==

' --- SCENARIO 2: COMPLIANCE ---
box "Scenario B: Clean Architecture Compliance" #LightGreen
    participant "High-Level Module\n<b>(Domain Layer)" as Domain_Good
    participant "Interface\n<b>(Application Boundary)" as Interface
    participant "Adapter\n<b>(Infrastructure Layer)" as Adapter
    participant "Low-Level Module\n<b>(External Service)" as Infra_Good
end box

Domain_Good -> Interface : <b>saveReport(data)</b>
activate Interface

Interface -> Adapter : <b>saveReport(data)</b>
activate Adapter

note right of Adapter
    **Clean Architecture:**
    Adapter acts as the
    **Anti-Corruption Layer**
    It translates Domain intent
    into Technical details.
end note

Adapter -> Infra_Good : <b>INSERT INTO...</b>
activate Infra_Good
Infra_Good --> Adapter : <b>ResultSet
deactivate Infra_Good

Adapter --> Interface : <b>Success
deactivate Adapter

Interface --> Domain_Good : <b>Confirmation
deactivate Interface

note right of Domain_Bad
    **Clean Code Violation:**
    Dependency Rule Broken
    (Domain depends on Infrastructure)
end note

note right of Domain_Good
    **DIP Respected:**
    High-Level defines the Interface.
    Low-Level conforms to it.
end note

@enduml